# Rule routing map

Use this table to decide which specialist rules apply. Rules with `globs` activate when matching files are open; for multi-domain work, treat every matching rule as active.

## When to apply each rule

| You are working on | Activate |
|--------------------|----------|
| TypeScript types, stores, hooks, services, performance | `technical-excellence.mdc` |
| UI components, screens, layout, styling, animations | `ui-ux-design.mdc` |

## Skills

Project skills live in `.cursor/skills/{name}/SKILL.md`. Read the matching skill when the trigger applies.

| Skill | Trigger |
|-------|---------|
| `add-i18n-key` | Any user-visible string is added or changed |
| `add-screen` | Creating a new Expo Router screen or page |

## Maintenance contract

**New rule:** add `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` with a tight `globs` pattern, then add a row to the table above. **New skill:** add `.cursor/skills/{name}/SKILL.md`, then add a row here. Do not broaden existing `globs` — prefer narrow patterns and this table for orientation.
